==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sheeps-eye
<hw>Sheep's"-eye`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A modest,
diffident look; a loving glance; -- commonly in the plural.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I saw her just now give him the languishing eye, as they call it;
. . . of old called the <qex>sheep's-eye</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Wycherley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

